text:
Iran Conducted Ballistic Missile Launch on Sunday Share Share Tweet 
The Islamic Republic of Iran conducted a nuclear ballistic missile test on Sunday, according to Fox News . 
The action would be a direct violation of the UN resolution and would go against Barack Obama's "Iran Deal" filed in 2016. 
The launch occurred at a well-known test site outside Semnan, about 140 miles east of Tehran. The missile was a Khorramshahr medium range ballistic missile and traveled 600 miles before exploding, in a failed test of a reentry vehicle, officials said. Fox News learns Iran conducted ballistic missile launch Sunday in apparent violation of UN resolution #FoxNews
